    "body": "I'm probably missing something here, but how would the `Text` trait actually be used? If we implement it in `extra::encoding::Base64`, `extra::encoding::Hex`, etc, I would think that it would cause a duplicate trait implementation error, and even if it didn't, how would the user select the encoding they want? You could differentiate with a dummy type parameter, but I'm not sure why `str.encode::<Base64Tag>(...)` is any better than `str.to_base64(...)`.\n",
