    "body": "The name `encoding::Text` is OK but I feel it's not the best name we could use.\nIf I'm new to Rust and install a new version of Rust including `extra::encoding` as in current draft, I would think `extra::encoding::Text` handles character encodings such as UTF-8. (it's not a joke; Haskell's [Data.Text.Encoding](http://hackage.haskell.org/packages/archive/text/0.11.3.1/doc/html/Data-Text-Encoding.html) does.)\n",
